\pard\plain \intbl\itap1\sa160\qj{\f1\fs20\b1 Quick Bit}{\f0\fs22  The name Abram means \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Exalted Father.\u8221\'94 The name Abraham is explained in Gen 17:5 as meaning \u8220\'93father of a multitude of nations.\u8221\'94 This meaning for Abraham is probably based on the wordplay between }{\f0\fs22\i1 av}{\f0\fs22  (\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93father\u8221\'94) and the words }{\f0\fs22\i1 raham}{\f0\fs22  and }{\f0\fs22\i1 hamon}{\f0\fs22 , both of which mean \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93multitude.\u8221\'94 This name served a daily reminder of Abraham\u8217\'92s ultimate destiny.}
\par\plain \intbl\itap1\f0\fs24\cell{
\trowd\trgaph0 \trautofit1\lastrow \trbrdrt\brdrnil \trbrdrr\brdrnil \trbrdrb\brdrnil \trbrdrl\brdrnil 
