\par\pard\plain \sa160\sb360\ql\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs32 Application}
\par\pard\plain \sa160\sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24 The story of Abraham and Sarah\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s life is not simply about the unfolding of God\u8217\'92s promise and faithfulness to the patriarchal couple; it is the story of God revealing Himself to those attempting to follow His promise. It is a story of discovering God\u8217\'92s character.}
\par\pard\plain \sa180\sb180\qj\ltrch\loch \f0\fs24
\par\pard\plain \fi360\sa160\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24 When God called Abraham out of Ur, Abraham unquestioningly followed Him (Gen 12:1). Yet decades later, when God announced that Sarah would have a son in her old age, both Abraham and Sarah responded with laughter, unable to suppress their doubt (Gen 17:17; 18:12). Abraham and Sarah didn\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t have the full picture of God\u8217\'92s plan, but their laughter also revealed that they did not have a full understanding of the extent of God\u8217\'92s power. They had not yet learned that nothing is too difficult for Yahweh (Gen 18:14).}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24 When faced with challenges in our journey of faith, it may become difficult to imagine how God\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s unlimited ability will pull us through. When we experience loss or pain, we may be unable to place our confidence in God\u8217\'92s goodness. In these cases, we can turn to the Bible to see how God\u8217\'92s power and grace manifested in the lives of those who followed Him. The Bible does not simply describe God\u8217\'92s involvement with humankind\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 it describes who God is. And, like Abraham and Sarah, we can grow in our understanding of God\u8217\'92s character as He reveals Himself to us in the story of our lives.}
\par\pard\plain \sa160\sb360\ql\ltrch\loch {\f3\fs24\i1 Study Questions}
\par\pard\plain \tx360\li360\fi-360\sa160\sb180\ql\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24 1.\tab When have you ever responded in laughter to God\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s promise in your own life? How has God convinced you of His omnipotence?}
\par\pard\plain \li360\sa160\sb180\ql\ltrch\loch \f0\fs24
\par\pard\plain \tx360\li360\fi-360\sa160\sb180\ql\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24 2.\tab How does thinking about the Bible as a description of God\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s character change your view of God\u8217\'92s Word? How does thinking of the Bible as a story that tells us who God is affect the way you view your life story?\{\\Scrv_fn=}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0  Grigoni, M. R., Custis, M., Mangum, D., & Whitehead, M. M. (2012). \\end_Scrv_fn\}\{\\Scrv_fn=}{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://ref.ly/logosres/csabraham?ref=Bible.Ge17.1-18.15&off=18743"}{\fldrslt\f5\fs24\b0\i1\ul\ulc0\cf4 Abraham: Following God\loch\af5\hich\af5\dbch\af5\uc1\u8217\'92s Promise\\end_Scrv_fn\}\{\\Scrv_fn=}}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0  (Ge 17:1\endash 18:15). Bellingham, WA: Lexham Press.\\end_Scrv_fn\}}
